explanation: The original program never handled the case for N between 10^8 and 10^9-1 (it was missing the branch that truncates the last 6 digits). Instead of adding another branch (which would require changing or adding lines), I replaced the single input line with a one-line, general formula: compute the number of digits d = len(str(n)) and, if d > 3, truncate the last (d-3) digits by subtracting n % (10**(d-3)). This fixes the missing case and correctly covers all ranges with exactly one changed line. (No retrieved diff was directly applicable to this fix.)
